d share workbooks, and move on to manipulating data and working with rows and columns.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll also modify your worksheets by formatting cells, text and numbers, align cell contents, search for and replace data, and spell check a worksheet. You\u2019ll end the week by learning how to print a workbook by adjusting page layout and print options.<\/p>\n<p>In Week 2, you\u2019ll learn Excel\u2019s syntax for writing formulas and functions, and learn how to implement and use formulas and functions with data in Excel. Formulas and functions form the backbone of Excel.<\/p>\n<p>Almost anything you\u2019ll do in Excel will require formulas and functions, that\u2019s why they are absolutely indispensable. You\u2019ll then sort and filter data, define data sets by applying range names, and work with specialized functions, text functions and logical functions.<\/p>\n<p>Next, in Week 3, you\u2019ll move on to organizing and visualizing data in Excel. You\u2019ll learn how to create, format and modify tables and charts, use database functions, manage worksheets and workbooks, understand advanced chart elements such as trendlines.<\/p>\n<p>Trendlines are lines that you can add on your charts to represent the flow of data (in other words, the \u201ctrend\u201d). You can also think of this as the best-fit curve. Then, you\u2019ll analyze data using pivot tables and slicers.<\/p>\n<p>Week 4 will teach you how to use some advanced Excel features such as customizing formulas by applying conditional formatting, proofing and saving, customizing the Excel interface, and enhancing workbooks and managing workbook properties.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll also take a look at exporting data and use various data sources to import useful data.<\/p>\n<p>There is an optional \u201cHonors\u201d week at the end of the course. Week 5 will give you an opportunity to put your Excel skills to the test by completing a peer-graded project. Passing this will give you the special \u201cHonors\u201d badge on your certificate!<\/p>\n<h3>How You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>The course is broken down into 5 weeks. Each week involves about 4 to 5 hours of work. Concepts are taught through a combination of videos and readings.<\/p>\n<p>As I said earlier, the videos are very concise and professional. The readings include step-by-step instructions to practice exercise. All necessary files are provided neatly under the \u201cResources\u201d section of the course.<\/p>\n<p>Along with the readings, there are ample ungraded practice quizzes in each week to test your knowledge before you attempt the graded quizzes. At the very end, there is an optional \u201cHonors\u201d assignment consisting of two tasks. You\u2019ll need to apply all that you\u2019ve learned in this course to complete them.<\/p>\n<p>The first task lets you demonstrate your skills of working with formulas and functions, modifying worksheets, and managing and printing workbooks. You\u2019ll also be able to show that you can analyze data and use charts to visualize data. The second task, you\u2019ll have to review the same assignment done by a peer and provide constructive feedback.<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Institution<\/td>\n<td>Microsoft<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Provider<\/td>\n<td>Coursera<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Level<\/td>\n<td>Beginner<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Workload<\/td>\n<td>20 hours<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Enrollments<\/td>\n<td>13K<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Rating<\/td>\n<td>4.7\/5.0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Certificate<\/td>\n<td>Paid<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h3>Fun Facts<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">This course is the second of the three courses in the Microsoft <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/microsoft-365-fundamentals-89482\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">365 Fundamentals Specialization<\/a>.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>If you\u2019re interested in this course, you can find <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/microsoft-excel-work-smarter-60110