rksheets. Then you\u2019ll understand data filtering in Excel, and construct and use pivot tables (powerful data summarization tools) to organize data. You\u2019ll also be introduced to creating graphs and charts in Excel for data visualization.<\/p>\n<p>Finally, in Week 4, you\u2019ll end the course by learning more about graphs and charts in Excel. You\u2019ll learn about advanced graphs and charts such as\u00a0 line graphs, bar graphs and pie charts. You\u2019ll also take a look at pivot charts, scatter plots and histograms.<\/p>\n<h3>How You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>The course is broken down into 4 weeks. Each week involves about 3 to 4 hours of work. Concepts are taught through a combination of videos and a lot of practice exercises.<\/p>\n<p>Each video is dedicated to a particular functionality of Excel. There is a good balance of theory and examples. The instructor, Sharad Borle, explains each topic briefly using slides before moving on to hands-on demonstration.<\/p>\n<p>After each and every video, there\u2019s an ungraded practice quiz to test your knowledge. This means there are ample practice opportunities in this course, which is definitely a plus point! Finally, at the end of each week, there\u2019s a graded quiz that adds to your final score.<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Institution<\/td>\n<td>Rice University<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Provider<\/td>\n<td>Coursera<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instructor<\/td>\n<td>Sharad Borle<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Level<\/td>\n<td>Beginner<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Workload<\/td>\n<td>20 hours<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Enrollments<\/td>\n<td>219K<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Rating<\/td>\n<td>4.7\/5.0 (9.3K)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Certificate<\/td>\n<td>Paid<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h3>Fun Facts<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">This course is the first of the five courses in the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/business-statistics-analysis-18816\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Business