k for the best Microsoft Excel online course is the <b>free-to-audit<\/b> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/excel-basics-data-analysis-ibm-21538\"><i>Excel Basics for Data Analysis<\/i><\/a>, offered by IBM on Coursera.<\/p>\n<p>IBM always provides crisp and to-the-point courses, and this one is no exception. With clear visuals and IBM\u2019s interactive AI-generated voice, these courses never fail to draw attention to the materials taught. And there\u2019s nothing better than learning Excel from the computer experts. So make sure to check this one out!<\/p>\n<p>A commendable feature of this course (as is the case with many IBM courses) is the use of something known as a \u201cHands-on Lab\u201d. These are fun practice exercises about which I\u2019ll talk more in the subsequent sections.<\/p>\n<h3>What You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>In Week 1, you\u2019ll learn about the basics of spreadsheets, spreadsheet terminology, the spreadsheet interface, and navigating your way around worksheets and workbooks.<\/p>\n<p>Week 2 covers basic spreadsheet tasks such as viewing, entering and editing data, and moving, copying and filling data. You\u2019ll also take a look at the fundamentals of Excel formulas, and the most common functions used by a data analyst. You\u2019ll end the week by learning how to reference data in formulas.<\/p>\n<p>Moving on, in Week 3, you\u2019ll learn about the importance of data quality. You\u2019ll learn about the fundamentals of data privacy, and how to import file data into Excel.<\/p>\n<p>Additionally, you\u2019ll understand how to remove duplicate and inaccurate data, and also remove empty rows in your data. You\u2019ll then learn to handle inconsistencies in your data, and finally, see the use of Flash Fill and Text to Columns features of Excel to manipulate and standardize your data.<\/p>\n<p>Week 4 deals with the fundamentals of analyzing data using spreadsheets. Here, you\u2019ll learn how to filter and sort data, and use some of the most useful Excel functions. You\u2019ll take a closer look at the VLOOKUP and HLOOKUP functions, and create and use pivot tables in Excel.<\/p>\n<p>Finally, in Week 5, there\u2019s a peer-graded assignment that will add to your final grade.<\/p>\n<h3>How You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>The course is broken down into 5 weeks. Each week involves about 2 to 3 hours of work. Concepts are taught through a combination of videos, readings, practice exercises and hands-on labs.<\/p>\n<p>The video lectures and demonstrations are professionally built, with an AI voice guiding you through the course. They present all the information to you clearly using quality presentations and examples.<\/p>\n<p>There are ungraded practical exercises throughout the course. Along with that, there are \u201cHands-on Labs\u201d too. These are ungraded practical exercises, but not in the form of quizzes. You\u2019ll first need to download the Excel file provided and then go through the instructions to solve the problems on your own computer.<\/p>\n<p>There are graded quizzes after each module, and at the end of the course, there is a peer-graded assignment. Once you complete the hands-on labs of Week 5, you\u2019ll have to submit those Excel files for your peers to evaluate.<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Institution<\/td>\n<td>IBM<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Provider<\/td>\n<td>Coursera<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instructor<\/td>\n<td>Sandip Saha Joy, Steve Ryan<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Level<\/td>\n<td>Beginner<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Workload<\/td>\n<td>12 hours<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Enrollments<\/td>\n<td>96.3K<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Rating<\/td>\n<td>4.8\/5.0 (2.8K)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Certificate<\/td>\n<td>Paid<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>If you\u2019re interested in this course, you can find <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/excel-basics-data-analysis-ibm-21538\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">more information about the course and how to enroll here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"anchor-10\">10. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/datacamp-data-analysis-in-excel-24399\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Data Analysis in Excel (DataCamp)<\/a><\/h2>\n<figure id=\"attachment_80323\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-80323\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-80323\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/10.-Data-Analysis-in-Excel-DataCamp.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/10.-Data-Analysis-in-Excel-DataCamp.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/10.-Data-Analysis-in-Excel-DataCamp-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/10.-Data-Analysis-in-Excel-DataCamp-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-80323\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The process of data analysis in Excel<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>My tenth pick for the best Microsoft Excel online course is <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/datacamp-data-analysis-in-excel-24399\"><em>Data Analysis in Excel<\/em><\/a>, offered by DataCamp.<\/p>\n<p>Perhaps the shortest one on this list, this course is no less productive than its preceding ones. Designed in a slightly different fashion, this course is actually broken down into three \u201cchapters\u201d. I\u2019ll talk more about how this works in the subsequent sections. And the coolest feature of this course is that you\u2019ll get to use spreadsheets on your browser!<\/p>\n<p>The instructor starts the course by telling a short story of how she came to use Excel. This is a nice personal touch since many of you will be able to relate to it and realize that learning Excel is not all that daunting!<\/p>\n<p>DataCamp understands that Excel is used as much in institutions as in companies. That\u2019s why they\u2019ll make sure that you\u2019re ready with all the Excel skills that you need in order to be industry-ready.<\/p>\n<h3>What You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>The very first (free) chapter will take you through the very basics of Excel and using Excel to analyze data. You\u2019ll start off by looking at all the different things Excel is capable of, check out the data analysis steps, set up your spreadsheet environment, and navigate your way through worksheets.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll explore data in Excel, learn to look for exact matches, trim excess data, and sort data in tables. You\u2019ll then move on Excel functions, learn about nesting of functions, and understand the different types of data Excel can handle. Finally, you\u2019ll learn how to classify data types, change other data types to text, and round off decimal values.<\/p>\n<p>In the next chapter, you\u2019ll move on to data cleaning and preparing text and date fields. You\u2019ll also learn about some of the most popular Excel functions including VLOOKUP. You\u2019ll begin by handling text data. This includes cleaning text data, joining text strings, capitalizing words, using upper and lower case, extracting text from cells, and replacing characters.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll then work with date data by preparing date data, finding the day of the week, and figuring out the month. You\u2019ll then learn about some of the most essential functions in Excel, and use them to find matching columns, work with range_lookup, and finally, use the VLOOKUP function.<\/p>\n<p>In the final chapter, you\u2019ll use advanced Excel tools to analyze data. You\u2019ll work with the COUNT function and use it in different scenarios, and take a look at Excel\u2019s capabilities as a calculator. In other words, you\u2019ll learn to use the math functions of Excel. You\u2019ll also be able to use functions to find the minimum value in a dataset, and aggregate data.<\/p>\n<p>You\u2019ll then learn about the logic functions in Excel. You\u2019ll understand the arguments of the IF function, perform logical tests using the IF function, and apply it in more complex tasks. Then, you\u2019ll perform conditional aggregations, find unique values in a dataset, count projects, and determine the average of a set of values.<\/p>\n<h3>How You\u2019ll Learn<\/h3>\n<p>As I mentioned earlier, the course is broken down into three chapters, and each chapter contains several subtopics. Each chapter involves about 1 to 2 hours of work. Concepts are taught through a combination of videos and interactive quizzes.<\/p>\n<p>Videos are short, simple and easy to understand. There are two types of quizzes in this course: multiple choice and drag-and-drop. I found these really fun and different from the usual quizzes other courses generally have.<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Provider<\/td>\n<td>DataCamp<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instructor<\/td>\n<td>Jen Bricker<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Level<\/td>\n<td>Beginner<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Workload<\/td>\n<td>4 hours<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Enrollments<\/td>\n<td>94K<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Certificate<\/td>\n<td>Paid<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h3>One Thing to Note<\/h3>\n<p>Only the first chapter, Exploring Data, has free access. To get the next two chapters, you\u2019ll need to have a Premium account. But as much as we are a fan of free content, we also know that some things are worth paying for.<\/p>\n<p>If you\u2019re interested in this course, you can find <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/course\/datacamp-data-analysis-in-excel-24399\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">more information about the course and how to enroll here<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Here is a guide with the best Microsoft Excel online courses and trainings (including free ones) to master the fundamentals and beyond.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":102,"featured_media":81403,"comment